name: Community Health Centers of Burlington
notes: Largest FQHC in the Burlington area; provides primary care, dental, behavioral health, and substance abuse services across multiple sites in Chittenden County.

name: Fenway Health
notes: FQHC known for LGBTQIA+ health focus; provides primary care, behavioral health, dental, pharmacy, and HIV/AIDS services. Founded 1971.

name: Joseph P. Addabbo Family Health Center
notes: Multi-site FQHC serving Queens and Brooklyn communities; provides adult/family medicine, dental, behavioral health, pediatrics, and women's health.

name: Penobscot Community Health Care
notes: Largest FQHC in Maine; provides primary care, dental, behavioral health, and pharmacy services across multiple sites in the Greater Bangor area.

name: Philadelphia FIGHT Community Health Centers
notes: FQHC providing primary care, dental, behavioral health, and HIV/Hepatitis C specialty care; serves diverse urban populations with sliding fee scale.

name: Community Health Center, Inc.
notes: One of the largest FQHCs in Connecticut, serving over 145,000 patients; provides primary care, dental, and behavioral health across multiple locations statewide. Founded 1972.
